title: Salomé Zourabichvili - Wikipedia
snippet: Salomé Nino Zourabichvili (born 18 March 1952) is a French-born Georgian politician and former diplomat who served as the fifth president of Georgia, becoming the first female to be elected as president in the country's history.

title: Georgia's outgoing president Salome Zourabichvili refuses to quit as successor Mikheil Kavelashvili sworn in
snippet: Mikheil Kavelashvili (left) was sworn in as Georgia's president on Sunday. Outgoing president Salome Zourabichvili (right) has refused to recognise his appointment

title: Salome Zourabichvili – Warsaw Security Forum
snippet: From 2010 to 2015, she also chaired the United Nations Security Council monitoring group on sanctions against Iran. In 2016, Zourabichvili was elected as an independent Deputy in the Parliament of Georgia.
